# License Check Ignore File
# Exclude packages from license compliance checks
#
# Use this file to:
# - Ignore false positives from license scanners
# - Exclude packages that have been manually reviewed
# - Skip packages with custom/approved license agreements
#
# Format: One package name per line
# Comments start with #

# =============================================================================
# Dev-only packages (not included in production builds)
# =============================================================================
# These packages are only used during development and don't need strict
# license compliance for production use.

# Testing frameworks (example)
# jest
# mocha
# chai
# pytest

# Linters (example)
# eslint
# prettier

# =============================================================================
# Manually reviewed packages
# =============================================================================
# These packages have been reviewed and approved by legal/compliance.
# Document the review date and approver.

# Reviewed: 2024-01-15 by Legal Team
# some-package-with-custom-license

# =============================================================================
# Dual-licensed packages
# =============================================================================
# Packages with dual licensing where we're using the permissive option.
# Document which license we're using.

# Using MIT license (also available under GPL)
# some-dual-licensed-package

# =============================================================================
# Internal/first-party packages
# =============================================================================
# Packages owned by our organization that don't need external license review.

# @myorg/*

# =============================================================================
# False positives
# =============================================================================
# Packages incorrectly flagged by license scanners.
# Document why it's a false positive.

# License scanner misidentifies, actual license is MIT
# some-mislabeled-package
